The West German leader advocates a reunified Germany that would respect the security needs _ and borders _ of the rest of Europe. The rallies came shortly after the four victorious World War II Allies met in West Berlin to discuss the latest developments in East Germany and Berlin _ the divided city that they still technically administer. The paper repeated the Communists' promise to work for a new democratic socialism within a multi-party system. The Communist Party today admitted that East Germany's socialist system has failed, and expressed support for a type of partnership with West Germany. 